title: "R–RPE: An Identity‑Projected Reward Prediction Error Achieving Over 60% Reduction in LLM Hedging"
authors:
  - family-names: Lu
    given-names: Louis J.
    affiliation: Independent Researcher, Claritism
    email: louis.j@claritism.org
date-released: 2025-09-15
version: preprint
type: report
repository-code: https://github.com/louisjmakise/rrpe-parameter-golf
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.17118156
abstract: |
  We introduce R–RPE, an identity-projected extension of Reward Prediction Error that adds a pre-action appraisal divergence between a predicted external evaluation distribution and a self-narrative prior. In evaluation-only experiments, R–RPE reduces hedging by more than 60% while maintaining utility.
